Larger than male. FWs short, little recovering, reaching tergite 1 (
Fig. 11B
). Dorsal field with six to eight longitudinal veins, lateral field with four longitudinal veins. Subgenital plate distal margin deeply sinuate. Ovipositor as long or slightly longer than FIII, but longer than TIII.
